=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heartjoys>heartjoys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=purple><b>Velvet-Steel Wannabe</b></font></span><br>  Posts: 1897<br> <font color=#B87333>(12/4/03 1:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://heartjoys.fcpages.com/Sparrow'sHearth/celticcross.jpeg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Monument of Ten Commandments</span><hr size=1> Jim:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Why would an all-powerful God be jealous? That is a human trait.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
from the Hebrew: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>quana</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: when God is the subject of the verb <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>qana'</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the meaning is 'be zealous', and the preposition <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>le</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (to, for) is used before the object;  His holy name (Eze 39:25) His land (Joel 2:18) and His inheritance (Zec 1:14)  Zec 8:2 &quot;Thus saith the Lord of hosts;  I was jealous for Zion with great jealousy, and I was jealous for her with great fury&quot;<br>
<br>
The verb for 'envy' is nowhere attributed to God in the Old Testament.  So, meanings of the words used in scripture is important to understand.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Why does Christianity not accept any other religion? (And in some cases, Protestants do not accept Catholics, and vice versa.) Are Christian beliefs so fragile that they do not hold up when there are other ideas to compare them to? This intolerance and non-acceptance of other religions is one important reason that many of us resist any government attempts to endorse and promote Christianity.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
All religions (even that of unbelief) are exclusive.  There is a difference in 'tolerating' another's beliefs and 'accepting' them as truth.<br>
<br>
I don't think you are looking at the core of the doctrine you believe if you think that other religions are 'tolerant'.  If they are built on a firm foundation, you need to examine it closely; if it appears that the doctrine is accepting of many various ideas and philosophies, there is no foundation.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Because some people are trying to force those commandments (such as the first one) on all of us.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Are you a law abiding citizen?  Do you feel protected by our laws?  That no one may rob you or injure you without penalty?  What would you attribute moral law to?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> ..was referring to centuries of rule by the (Catholic) Church in Europe, where Jews and &quot;heretics&quot; were routinely sentenced to death for their beliefs, because those beliefs did not match the Church's beliefs. (Inquisition, witch burnings, etc.) Also, some of today's Islamic countries do similar things (especially in Afghanistan when the Taliban was ruling).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, I agree with you that men of power use religion for their own evil means.  That is a sad reality of world history.  But that fact has nothing to do with the truth found in the Gospel of Jesus Christ.  The truth stands alone- that men may fall and misuse the tenants of Christianity has nothing to do with the truth as spoken and lived by Jesus Christ.  You have to examine what is written there, not rely on half-truths and misdeeds of men.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
